gov.sandia.cognition.learning.data

Interface WeightedInputOutputPair<InputType,OutputType>

  • Type Parameters:
    InputType - The type for the input object in the pair.
    OutputType - The type for the output object in the pair.
    All Superinterfaces:
    InputOutputPair<InputType,OutputType>, Pair<InputType,OutputType>, java.io.Serializable, Weighted, WeightedPair<InputType,OutputType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultWeightedInputOutputPair

    @CodeReview(reviewer="Justin Basilico",
            date="2006-10-04",
            changesNeeded=false,
            comments="Simple container class looks fine.")
public interface WeightedInputOutputPair<InputType,OutputType>
extends InputOutputPair<InputType,OutputType>, WeightedPair<InputType,OutputType>
    The WeightedInputOutputPair class implements an additional weighting term on an InputOutputPair, typically used to inform learning algorithms of the relative weight between examples.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
